						               													<description>A 3 player, 9-card game. At the beginning of the game, each player will draw 3 random cards from a deck of 9, and look at them. Each card is given a number of cubes that are placed on said card, these cubes serve as health, for example, kings have 6 health cubes, Queens have 5, Jacks have 4, and all other cards have 3. Each round, players have to place 1 or 2 cards of their choosing in their &amp;ldquo;card placing section&amp;rdquo;. Each time a player does this, they lose a piece of &amp;ldquo;health&amp;rdquo; on each of their placed cards (marked by moving the cube to resemble that its value has decreased by 1, ex: moving 6 to 5). After every turn, each player has to give one of their cards to the player in the clockwise direction. Once a card&amp;rsquo;s health reaches 0, the card is flipped over to show that it can&amp;rsquo;t be used anymore, it is then placed in the middle along with its health cube. Once a player&amp;rsquo;s entire deck is obsolete/can&amp;rsquo;t be used anymore, they&amp;rsquo;re out, and the last card standing wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
